        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:47AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 547 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jones Creek, or 7 miles southwest of Lake Jackson, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Jackson, Angleton, Freeport, Clute, West Columbia, Sweeny,
Surfside Beach, Richwood, Brazoria, Jones Creek, Oyster Creek,
Holiday Lakes, Bailey's Prairie, Sargent, and Wild Peach Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
